01:01.196 --> 01:03.197
♪ I've seen it all

01:03.231 --> 01:04.532
♪ All before

01:04.566 --> 01:05.900
♪ It's the new black

01:05.934 --> 01:08.001
♪ Yeah

01:08.036 --> 01:09.637
♪ What you want

01:09.671 --> 01:11.372
Vincent?

01:11.406 --> 01:12.806
♪ Me to do

01:12.840 --> 01:14.341
♪ Now you got...

01:14.376 --> 01:16.143
What are you doing here?

01:16.178 --> 01:17.545
Is everything
okay?

01:17.579 --> 01:19.012
Did Sam do something?

01:19.047 --> 01:20.481
No, this isn't about Sam.

01:20.515 --> 01:22.082
Oh.

01:22.116 --> 01:23.384
Where's Gabe?

01:23.418 --> 01:24.818
I came alone.

01:24.852 --> 01:26.053
I wanted to talk.

01:26.087 --> 01:28.055
Okay. About?

01:28.089 --> 01:28.854
About us.

01:28.879 --> 01:30.603
I didn't think
there was an us anymore.

01:30.925 --> 01:32.859
Do you want there to be?

01:36.297 --> 01:38.732
♪ It's the new black

01:40.767 --> 01:43.203
♪ And what is that?

01:56.450 --> 01:57.717
<i>Vincent?</i>

01:57.751 --> 01:59.118
<i>You called him Vincent?</i>

01:59.152 --> 02:00.552
Wow.

02:00.587 --> 02:01.921
And Gabe reacted how,
exactly?

02:01.955 --> 02:03.522
He just smiled.

02:03.556 --> 02:05.091
Smiled as in

02:05.125 --> 02:06.491
he just let it go,

02:06.526 --> 02:08.193
or smiled as in he
wanted to kill you

02:08.228 --> 02:09.661
right then and there?
I think it was the former,

02:09.696 --> 02:11.163
but it could've been the latter.

02:11.198 --> 02:13.132
Wait, it didn't happen during...

02:13.166 --> 02:14.466
No! No.

02:14.500 --> 02:15.834
It happened at dinner,
thank God.

02:15.868 --> 02:18.370
After a few too many margaritas,
obviously.

02:18.404 --> 02:21.440
Gabe is very understanding.
Mm.

02:21.474 --> 02:22.841
I, on the
other hand,

02:22.875 --> 02:24.109
would've gotten
on the next plane

02:24.143 --> 02:25.444
and flown
straight home.

02:25.478 --> 02:27.045
But I'm not the
forgiving type.

02:27.079 --> 02:28.313
Probably why
I'm still single.

02:28.348 --> 02:29.548
Tess, it was an
innocent mistake.

02:29.582 --> 02:31.049
Habit.

02:31.083 --> 02:32.784
And it's not like it
was supposed to be

02:32.818 --> 02:33.952
a romantic
getaway anyway.

02:33.986 --> 02:35.887
What? It wasn't.

02:35.921 --> 02:38.223
We had to make Sam think
that Gabe was really dead,

02:38.257 --> 02:39.557
we took off, that's all.

02:39.591 --> 02:40.792
To Cancun.

02:40.826 --> 02:42.227
You stayed in
a luxury resort,

02:42.261 --> 02:43.494
you got
massages,

02:43.528 --> 02:44.562
you made love...
Okay.

02:44.596 --> 02:45.897
Fine.

02:45.931 --> 02:47.865
It was a little romantic,
all right?

02:47.899 --> 02:50.468
And clearly I still have
issues with Vincent.

02:50.502 --> 02:51.835
Clearly.

02:51.870 --> 02:53.170
It's just hard to let it go

02:53.204 --> 02:54.405
after everything
we've been through.

02:54.439 --> 02:56.006
All the more reason why I need

02:56.040 --> 02:57.241
to stay away from him
for a while.

02:57.276 --> 02:58.133
Gabe?

02:58.134 --> 02:59.101
Vincent.

02:59.135 --> 03:00.602
I need some space,

03:00.636 --> 03:02.104
see if there's actually
a future with Gabe.

03:02.138 --> 03:03.938
Out of sight,
out of mind, right?

03:03.973 --> 03:05.206
Yeah, well, that's
easier said than done

03:05.240 --> 03:06.641
with all of us
trying to bust Sam.

03:06.675 --> 03:08.109
And, of course,
with Gabe dead...

03:10.646 --> 03:14.115
Gabriel Lowan
was a man of peace,

03:14.149 --> 03:15.717
a man who stood up to evil

03:15.751 --> 03:17.318
and faced it head-on.

03:17.352 --> 03:20.488
A man of strength,
a man of courage.

03:20.522 --> 03:22.289
Unafraid and unwilling...
Good thing he doesn't know

03:22.324 --> 03:23.724
about the beast part.
Shh.

03:23.758 --> 03:25.893
What?
We are at a funeral.

03:25.927 --> 03:27.628
Gabe's not really
dead, remember?

03:27.662 --> 03:29.897
Yeah, well, Sam needs
to think that he is.

03:29.931 --> 03:31.365
Yea, though I walk

03:31.400 --> 03:33.200
through the valley of
the shadow of death,

03:33.235 --> 03:34.201
for thou art with me.

03:34.236 --> 03:35.503
Act a little sad,
will you?

03:35.537 --> 03:36.904
The only thing
I'm sad about

03:36.938 --> 03:38.705
is that I froze my
butt off to get here.

03:38.740 --> 03:40.240
Clearly, I'm not
the only one.

03:40.274 --> 03:42.643
Yeah, I think Gabe
expected a better turnout.

03:42.677 --> 03:43.844
Let's not tell him.

03:45.947 --> 03:46.980
Hi.

03:47.015 --> 03:48.682
Hi.
Excuse me.

03:48.716 --> 03:51.151
...thou hast anointed
my head with oil...

03:51.185 --> 03:52.552
Sorry.

03:52.586 --> 03:54.320
Surely, thy loving-kindness

03:54.355 --> 03:56.222
shall follow me all the days...

03:56.257 --> 03:57.524
How's
it going?

03:57.558 --> 03:59.359
Act sad, you're
at a funeral.

04:00.461 --> 04:03.063
But he's not
really dead.

04:05.332 --> 04:07.833
Be strong...

04:07.868 --> 04:09.401
You know, I'm sorry
I'm late,

04:09.436 --> 04:11.637
but I, uh,
I overslept.

04:11.672 --> 04:13.973
Rough night?

04:15.208 --> 04:16.776
Yeah, yeah,
you could say that.

04:16.810 --> 04:18.142
Yeah.

04:19.512 --> 04:21.581
You know, you were right,
Sam is here.

04:21.615 --> 04:24.416
Yeah, well, we knew
he thought Dana was dead.

04:24.451 --> 04:26.452
But I figured he'd want to make
sure that Gabe was dead,

04:26.486 --> 04:29.088
before he continued
with whatever his plan is.

04:29.122 --> 04:31.790
And hopefully we can track down
this Tony Barnes...

04:31.824 --> 04:33.892
Yeah, we can all move
on with our lives.

04:35.562 --> 04:37.929
So, how was
Mexico?

04:39.165 --> 04:40.532
<i>Caliente.</i>

04:47.974 --> 04:49.207
Detective Chandler.

04:49.241 --> 04:51.710
I just wanted to
offer my condolences.

04:51.744 --> 04:53.344
Despite
what he did,

04:53.378 --> 04:54.846
I am truly sorry
for your loss.

04:54.880 --> 04:57.015
Thank you.

04:57.049 --> 04:58.410
How are you holding
up, Mr. Landon?

04:58.417 --> 04:59.950
I don't know.

04:59.985 --> 05:05.189
Can't believe
Dana's really... gone.

05:05.224 --> 05:06.390
I...

05:06.425 --> 05:08.126
I just got her back, too.

05:08.160 --> 05:10.561
Well, I'm sure she's
in a better place.

05:10.596 --> 05:12.563
Any luck
finding the man

05:12.598 --> 05:13.797
responsible
for this?

05:13.832 --> 05:15.733
- Tony Barnes?
- No, sorry.

05:15.767 --> 05:17.234
No leads at all.

05:17.268 --> 05:19.136
The guy really knows
how to cover his tracks.

05:19.170 --> 05:21.238
Well...

05:21.272 --> 05:22.940
I guess we'll
just have

05:22.974 --> 05:25.109
to somehow find
a way to move on.

05:26.444 --> 05:28.211
Good luck.

05:28.246 --> 05:29.579
You, too.

05:29.614 --> 05:31.881
Don't lose him.

05:31.915 --> 05:34.917
Not a chance.

05:34.952 --> 05:36.753
I can't believe you're
just walking away.

05:36.787 --> 05:38.087
Oh, come on.

05:38.122 --> 05:39.822
I'm not about to
tell her how I feel

05:39.857 --> 05:41.090
at her boyfriend's
funeral.

05:41.125 --> 05:42.659
He's not
really dead.

05:42.693 --> 05:45.895
Whoa, okay, that's
beside the point, okay?

05:45.929 --> 05:49.632
You know it's not just
about wanting her.

05:49.667 --> 05:51.267
It's... it's more
than that, you know?

05:51.301 --> 05:52.835
Even if she
wasn't with Gabe,

05:52.870 --> 05:54.671
I'd still have to find
a way to prove to her

05:54.705 --> 05:56.272
that I would
never choose...

05:56.306 --> 05:58.007
beast again.

05:58.042 --> 06:00.476
But you are a beast,
at least partly.

06:00.510 --> 06:01.978
You can't change that.

06:02.012 --> 06:04.413
No, but I can at least

06:04.447 --> 06:07.516
somehow show her that
I can control it better.

06:08.785 --> 06:10.018
How are you going to do that?

06:10.053 --> 06:11.353
Go beast cold turkey?

06:11.388 --> 06:13.489
That's a really
good idea.

06:18.628 --> 06:20.563
Coming!

06:25.301 --> 06:27.202
Hey.
Hey.

06:27.236 --> 06:29.537
So... how was
my funeral?

06:29.572 --> 06:31.039
Touching.
You would've loved it.

06:31.074 --> 06:32.340
Yeah?
Lots of people?

06:32.374 --> 06:33.675
You know...

06:33.710 --> 06:35.243
we only threw it together
pretty last minute,

06:35.277 --> 06:36.611
it was really cold
outside, so...

06:36.645 --> 06:39.113
So <i>not</i> a lot of people.

06:39.147 --> 06:40.381
No, there
were people.

06:40.416 --> 06:41.616
There.

06:41.650 --> 06:43.084
How many?

06:43.118 --> 06:45.853
Okay, Gabe, first of all,

06:45.887 --> 06:47.355
you didn't actually die,

06:47.389 --> 06:48.590
so there's that.

06:48.624 --> 06:49.857
And secondly,

06:49.891 --> 06:51.125
we didn't give people
much notice,

06:51.159 --> 06:52.427
so they just...
they sent flowers.

06:52.461 --> 06:53.894
They sent a lot of flowers.

06:53.929 --> 06:55.295
I sent the flowers.

06:55.330 --> 06:56.931
Oh.

06:56.965 --> 06:59.200
Well, they were
beautiful.

06:59.234 --> 07:00.935
You are a lousy liar.

07:00.969 --> 07:04.004
But thanks for
caring enough to try.

07:04.039 --> 07:05.372
Did Sam show up, at least?

07:05.406 --> 07:07.441
Yes.
And I think he bought it, too.

07:07.475 --> 07:09.110
Tess is trailing him
as we speak.

07:09.144 --> 07:11.345
Good. 'Cause I am going
stir-crazy in here.

07:11.379 --> 07:13.680
The sooner we find
something concrete

07:13.715 --> 07:14.948
to nail Sam with,

07:14.982 --> 07:16.483
the sooner I can
be reborn... again.

07:16.517 --> 07:17.718
Any luck finding Tony Barnes?

07:17.752 --> 07:18.985
No, but get this...

07:19.019 --> 07:20.320
We don't know
much about him,

07:20.355 --> 07:21.688
except that he amassed
a huge fortune

07:21.723 --> 07:23.022
in Manhattan real estate.

07:23.057 --> 07:24.491
But he liquidated his estate

07:24.525 --> 07:25.726
right after Sam went missing.

07:25.760 --> 07:26.761
So?

07:26.786 --> 07:29.002
So, he's like a modern day
Howard Hughes.

07:29.529 --> 07:31.131
Nobody's seen Barnes since.

07:31.165 --> 07:33.085
Yet he's still buying things...
expensive things.

07:36.875 --> 07:38.404
Hey, Tess,
where are you?

07:38.405 --> 07:39.939
St. Benjamin's Hospital.

07:39.974 --> 07:41.841
Sam's visiting a patient here.

07:41.876 --> 07:43.809
Who?

07:43.843 --> 07:45.210
Someone in intensive care,

07:45.245 --> 07:47.280
the quarantine ward.

07:50.049 --> 07:51.284
Sam's leaving.
I gotta go.

07:51.318 --> 07:52.278
Okay. You stay with him,

07:52.298 --> 07:54.178
I'll figure out who's was
visiting him, and why.

07:54.287 --> 07:55.719
Quarantine?
What does that mean?

07:55.744 --> 07:56.689
I don't know,

07:56.690 --> 07:58.391
but I'm going to go to
the hospital and find out.

07:58.425 --> 08:00.159
Well, y-you
can't go alone.

08:00.193 --> 08:02.694
Why? Sam's already left.
He'll never see me.

08:02.728 --> 08:04.096
Yeah, but you don't know
who you're gonna find there.

08:04.130 --> 08:05.931
For all we know,
it could be Barnes.

08:05.965 --> 08:07.199
Okay, but I can
handle myself.

08:07.233 --> 08:08.801
Sam tried to blow us all up.

08:08.835 --> 08:10.468
He will do anything
to save his ass,

08:10.503 --> 08:11.970
including killing you.

08:12.005 --> 08:13.238
At least take Vincent.

08:13.273 --> 08:15.240
Vincent?
Yes, Vincent.

08:15.275 --> 08:16.775
He will protect you
if anything goes wrong.

08:16.809 --> 08:18.042
Plus, he knows that
hospital inside-out.

08:18.076 --> 08:19.744
Didn't he do his
residency there?

08:21.980 --> 08:24.749
Look, he is in our lives,
and he is not going anywhere.

08:24.784 --> 08:26.951
So unless you tell me
I have something to worry about,

08:26.985 --> 08:29.220
I won't.

08:38.663 --> 08:41.164
I gotta admit, I was a little
surprised that you called.

08:41.200 --> 08:42.633
It was
Gabe's idea.

08:42.667 --> 08:43.967
Really?
Yeah.

08:44.001 --> 08:45.402
All he cares about
is nailing Sam...

08:45.403 --> 08:46.938
which is all I
care about, too.

08:46.972 --> 08:48.306
Copy that.

08:48.340 --> 08:49.973
Look, don't go through
Admitting, okay?

08:50.007 --> 08:51.375
Too much red tape.

08:51.409 --> 08:53.210
Just flash your badge
at an E.R. nurse,

08:53.244 --> 08:55.111
and they'll let you through.
They're used to cops.

08:55.146 --> 08:56.547
Must feel like
old times here.

08:56.581 --> 08:59.049
Actually, it feels like
a whole lifetime ago.

08:59.083 --> 09:00.984
This one's stable,
but we got more inbound.

09:01.018 --> 09:02.252
Hey, guys, let's go.

09:04.589 --> 09:06.189
Unbelievable.

09:06.224 --> 09:07.423
What's the matter?
Unbelievable.

09:07.458 --> 09:08.691
Hey, buddy,
you okay?

09:08.726 --> 09:10.227
My stomach hurts.

09:10.261 --> 09:12.395
Okay, show me where.
Around here.

09:12.429 --> 09:14.130
Okay, just take
a deep breath in.

09:14.165 --> 09:15.565
Here?

09:15.599 --> 09:17.267
Okay, okay.

09:17.301 --> 09:18.634
You're gonna be fine,
hang in there, okay?

09:18.669 --> 09:20.203
What are you doing?

09:20.238 --> 09:21.905
He's not stable at all.

09:24.608 --> 09:26.208
Hey, orderly,
come here.

09:26.243 --> 09:27.610
Get this kid to the O.R.,
stat, okay?

09:27.644 --> 09:29.111
Here.

09:30.013 --> 09:31.514
Thanks, Doc.
Yeah, quickly.

09:36.587 --> 09:37.787
What?

09:37.821 --> 09:40.789
It's nice seeing the old you.

09:42.328 --> 09:46.328
